is_locked":0},"guid":"D7B76230DC9C11EA9D7EE7EDAD03798A","state_version_id":46,"steps":[],"document":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><div class = \"justify\" style = \"text-align:center\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;:UNDERLINE;\">ISOLATING CELLS IN LOUPE BROWSER<\/span><\/div><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Within Loupe Browser, you can follow these steps to isolate species specific cells. The example below isolates human cells.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><ol style = \"list-style-type: decimal;\"><\/ol><\/div><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/public\/25bf22a13d103d8b69b97d8ee83818d7c6dc61065027d9118c36f255d130e1e2\/chbvbbs7x.png\" \/><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>2. For the features, if you search for <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">\"sum\"<\/span><span>, then you should see the human and mouse sums.<\/span><\/div><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/public\/25bf22a13d103d8b69b97d8ee83818d7c6dc61065027d9118c36f255d130e1e2\/chbwbbs7x.png\" \/><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">3. Select human sum for the y-axis, and mouse sum for the x-axis<\/div><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/public\/25bf22a13d103d8b69b97d8ee83818d7c6dc61065027d9118c36f255d130e1e2\/chbxbbs7x.png\" \/><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">4. Now, make both axes logarithmic.<\/div><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/public\/25bf22a13d103d8b69b97d8ee83818d7c6dc61065027d9118c36f255d130e1e2\/chbybbs7x.png\" \/><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">5. The human and mouse cells should be well separated, and you can select the desired cells using the lasso tool.<\/div><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/public\/25bf22a13d103d8b69b97d8ee83818d7c6dc61065027d9118c36f255d130e1e2\/chbzbbs7x.png\" \/><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">6. Once you have a custom cluster of human cells, you can switch back to t-SNE visualization if you wish.<\/div><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/public\/25bf22a13d103d8b69b97d8ee83818d7c6dc61065027d9118c36f255d130e1e2\/chbubbs7x.png\" \/><\/div><\/div>","materials":[],"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><div class = \"justify\" style = \"text-align:center\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;:UNDERLINE;\">ISOLATING CELLS IN LOUPE BROWSER<\/span><\/div><\/div><\/div>","changed_on":1597238803}